        "timestamp": "2019-11-15 13:43:20.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Do you need this to specify wildcards on searches? I wonder would\n > it be better to have a separate searchkey class?\n\nThis value must be stored in the DB, in the \"supported types\" field of the PdpSubgroup.  I guess an option would be to introduce a new class, perhaps searchkey, and put that into \"supported types\", instead.  I'm open.",
